<h4>ComponentCore (CMS/CRM)</h4>
Developer: <a href='http://DreamStudio.com'>DreamStudio</a> &nbsp;
<!--
Documentation: <a href='<%=GetLink("/net/help/default.aspx")%>'>Website How-To's</a> / <a href='<%=GetLink("/net/admin/tools.aspx")%>'>Admin Tools</a><br />
-->
Shared processes for managing contacts, content, events, locations and partners using the Core Data Project architecture. 
An item-based table and object structure which reduces table complexity by tracking images, stats, interests, news and access levels using common processes.<br />
<hr />

<h4>PDF Generator</h4>
Developer: <a href="http://www.websupergoo.com">WebSuperGoo</a> &nbsp; Documentation: <a href="http://www.websupergoo.com/abcpdf-1.htm">ABC PDF</a><br />
Send any page in the site to a PDF file.  This component is used most extensively in the GeorgiaFacts site for Available Building reports and manufacturer directories.<br />
<hr />

<h4>AspNetEmail</h4>
Developer: <a href='http://advancedintellect.com'>Advanced Intellect</a> &nbsp; Documentation: <a href="http://www.aspnetemail.com">AspNetEmail.com</a><br />
AspNetEmail is an SMTP email component which allows email to be sent reliably from any .NET application including web pages, windows forms and web services.  
We use it when queuing up outgoing bulk email to support sending to millions of recipients.
<hr />

<h4>EntitySpaces</h4>
Developer: <a href="http://EntitySpaces.com">EntitySpaces.com</a> &nbsp;Documentation: <a href='http://www.entityspaces.net/portal/Documentation/QuickReference/tabid/87/Default.aspx'>Quick Reference Guide</a><br />
The EntitySpaces architecture is a persistence layer and business object system for the Microsoft .NET Framework.
<hr />

